[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: MIL-STD-498 SIOM (Software Installation and Operation Manual)

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1. Scope

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1.1 Identification

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SIOM-001
TITLE: Manual Identification
STATEMENT: This document shall be identified as the Software Installation and Operation Manual (SIOM) for the Satellite Communication Management System (SCMS), version 1.0.
RATIONALE: Proper manual identification ensures configuration management and user guidance.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 1.2 Manual overview

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SIOM-002
TITLE: Manual Purpose
STATEMENT: This manual shall provide software installation procedures, describe software operation and usage, and cover maintenance and troubleshooting procedures for system users.
RATIONALE: Comprehensive manual purpose ensures effective system deployment and operation.

[/SECTION]

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 2. Referenced documents

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SIOM-003
TITLE: Reference Standards
STATEMENT: This manual shall reference MIL-STD-498, system requirements documents, and operational procedures to provide comprehensive user guidance.
RATIONALE: Reference documents ensure consistency with system specifications and procedures.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 3. System overview

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SIOM-004
TITLE: Software Description
STATEMENT: The manual shall describe the SCMS software system and its components, specify system requirements and dependencies, and provide software architecture overview.
RATIONALE: System overview helps users understand system capabilities and operational environment.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4. Installation procedures

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4.1 Pre-installation requirements

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SIOM-005
TITLE: Prerequisites
STATEMENT: The manual shall specify hardware and software prerequisites, describe system preparation procedures, and include compatibility verification steps.
RATIONALE: Prerequisites ensure successful system installation and operation.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4.2 Installation process

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SIOM-006
TITLE: Installation Steps
STATEMENT: The manual shall provide step-by-step installation instructions, include configuration procedures, and describe installation verification methods.
RATIONALE: Detailed installation steps ensure reliable system deployment.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 4.3 Post-installation setup

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SIOM-007
TITLE: Setup Procedures
STATEMENT: The manual shall describe post-installation configuration, specify user account setup procedures, and include system integration steps.
RATIONALE: Post-installation setup ensures proper system configuration and user access.

[/SECTION]

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 5. Operation procedures

[SECTION]
TITLE: 5.1 System startup

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SIOM-008
TITLE: Startup Procedures
STATEMENT: The manual shall describe system startup procedures, specify initialization processes, and include startup verification steps.
RATIONALE: Startup procedures ensure proper system initialization and operation.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 5.2 Normal operations

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SIOM-009
TITLE: Operational Procedures
STATEMENT: The manual shall describe normal operational procedures, specify user interface usage, and include data management procedures.
RATIONALE: Operational procedures ensure effective system utilization and data management.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 5.3 System shutdown

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SIOM-010
TITLE: Shutdown Procedures
STATEMENT: The manual shall describe system shutdown procedures, specify data backup procedures, and include shutdown verification steps.
RATIONALE: Shutdown procedures ensure proper system termination and data protection.

[/SECTION]

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 6. Maintenance procedures

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SIOM-011
TITLE: Maintenance Activities
STATEMENT: The manual shall describe routine maintenance procedures, specify backup and recovery procedures, and include system monitoring procedures.
RATIONALE: Maintenance procedures ensure system reliability and operational continuity.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 7. Troubleshooting

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SIOM-012
TITLE: Problem Resolution
STATEMENT: The manual shall provide troubleshooting procedures, include common problem solutions, and describe escalation procedures for complex issues.
RATIONALE: Troubleshooting procedures ensure rapid problem resolution and system restoration.

[/SECTION]

[SECTION]
TITLE: 8. Notes

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: SIOM-013
TITLE: Manual Notes
STATEMENT: This installation and operation manual shall be maintained under configuration control with regular updates to reflect system changes and user feedback.
RATIONALE: Document maintenance ensures user guidance accuracy and system alignment.

[/SECTION]
